          <solution>
            <p>
              Do your best to identify two points on the line (which are not necessarily the plotted
              data points). With this line, it seems <m>(2000,17500)</m> and <m>(2020,23000)</m> are
              two such points.
            </p>
            <p>
              <me>
                \frac{\Delta y}{\Delta x}=\frac{(23000-17500)\,\text{diagnoses}}{(2020-2000)\,\text{yr}}=275\,\frac{\text{diagnoses}}{\text{yr}}
              </me>
